<li><strong>Interoperability: </strong>Integration with traditional financial systems allows for seamless interoperability between different payment networks, enabling businesses to tap into a wider pool of customers and partners.</li>



<li><strong>Regulatory compliance: </strong>Traditional financial systems are well-established and regulated, providing businesses with a familiar and compliant framework to operate within.</li>



<li><strong>Improved user experience:</strong> Integrating with traditional financial systems enables businesses to offer a familiar and user-friendly payment experience, reducing friction and increasing customer satisfaction.</li>
</ul>



